default3.1.
default&#xa0; 
defaultThe International Monetary Fund (IMF)
default uses the following definition for energy subsidies:
default&#xa0;
defaultEnergy subsidies comprise both consumer and producer subsidies. 
defaultConsumer subsidies arise when the prices paid by consumers, including both firms (intermediate consumption) and households (final consumption), are below a benchmark price, while producer subsidies arise when prices received by suppliers are above this benchmark 
default&#xa0;
